[00:19.84]I live in a very old town which is surrounded by beautiful woods.|我住在一个非常古老的城镇里，这个城镇被美丽的树林环绕着。
[00:28.00]It is a famous beauty spot.|这是一个著名的风景优美、景色宜人的地方。
[00:32.06]On Sundays, hundreds of people come from the city to see our town and to walk through the woods.|每到周日，都会有数百人从城里来到我们这个小镇，然后漫步在树林里。
[00:42.50]Visitors have been asked to keep the woods clean and tidy.|游客们被要求保持森林的整洁和干净。
[00:49.55]Litter baskets have been placed under the trees, but people still throw their rubbish everywhere.|虽然树底下已经放置了垃圾篓，人们仍然把垃圾扔得到处都是。
[00:58.99]Last Wednesday, I went for a walk in the woods.|上周三，我去树林里散步了。
[01:05.51]What I saw made me very sad.|我所看到的一切让我感到非常难过。
[01:10.74]I counted seven old cars and three old refrigerators.|我数了七辆旧汽车和三台旧冰箱。
[01:18.12]The little baskets were empty and the ground was covered with pieces of paper,|那些小篮子都是空的，地面上散落着许多纸片。
[01:25.80]cigarette ends, old tyres, empty bottles and rusty tins.|烟头、旧轮胎、空瓶子以及生锈的铁罐。
[01:34.49]Among the rubbish, I found a sign which said, 'Anyone who leaves litter in these woods will be prosecuted!'|在那些垃圾中，我发现了一张告示，上面写着：“任何在这些树林里乱扔垃圾的人都将受到法律追究！”
